    <item>
      <title>Mapping CSS Color Names to RGB and Hex Codes</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2024/03/01/mapping-css-color-names-to-rgb-and-hex-codes/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Mar 2024 19:54:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/2024/03/01/mapping-css-color-names-to-rgb-and-hex-codes/</guid>
      <category domain="http://localhost:1313/engineering/">Engineering</category>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently found myself needing to enforce color values in a hex code format after discovering a mix of hex codes and CSS color names in my data. The easiest way to do this was to build a static map. My application is built with PHP so I needed to get the full list of CSS color names as listed on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/#named-colors&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;external nofollow noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;W3&amp;rsquo;s website&lt;/a&gt; into an associative PHP array.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Using PHP&#39;s preg_filter to Easily Subdivide Arrays</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2020/12/29/using-phps-preg_filter-to-easily-subdivide-arrays/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Dec 2020 14:51:32 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/2020/12/29/using-phps-preg_filter-to-easily-subdivide-arrays/</guid>
      <category domain="http://localhost:1313/engineering/">Engineering</category>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;PHP&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.preg-filter.php&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;external nofollow noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;preg_filter&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; function is great for filtering array elements that match a given expression. The official documentation states that the function &amp;ldquo;only returns the (possibly transformed) subjects where there was a match&amp;rdquo; meaning if no elements match the given pattern, an empty array is returned (when dealing with an array of course).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For example, take an array of multiple type of entity types and their IDs:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;$ids = [123, &amp;#39;team:4&amp;#39;, 52, &amp;#39;pond:16&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;team:12&amp;#39;, 6];&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the array above, we have users (integer IDs), teams (prefixed by &amp;ldquo;team:&amp;rdquo;) and a &amp;ldquo;pond&amp;rdquo; entity prefixed by &amp;ldquo;pond:&amp;rdquo;. If we want to process teams and ponds we could use a traditional loop checking for prefixes and parsing out the integer IDs like so:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TIL how to use preg_filter() to add a prefix or suffix to array elements</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/2020/05/02/til-how-to-use-preg_filter-to-add-a-prefix-or-suffix-to-array-elements/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/2020/05/02/til-how-to-use-preg_filter-to-add-a-prefix-or-suffix-to-array-elements/</guid>
      <category domain="http://localhost:1313/engineering/">Engineering</category>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You can add a prefix or suffix to every element of an array succinctly using &lt;code&gt;preg_filter()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;5&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;6&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;7&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;8&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;?php&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;$ids = range(1, 5);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;$prefixedIds = preg_filter(&amp;#39;/^/&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;prefix_&amp;#39;, $ids);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;$suffixedIds = preg_filter(&amp;#39;/$/&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;_suffix&amp;#39;, $ids);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;print_r($prefixedIds);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;print_r($suffixedIds);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The print statements above will output:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 5&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 6&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 7&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 8&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 9&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;10&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;11&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;12&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;13&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;14&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;15&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;16&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;17&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Array&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [0] =&amp;gt; prefix_1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [1] =&amp;gt; prefix_2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [2] =&amp;gt; prefix_3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [3] =&amp;gt; prefix_4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [4] =&amp;gt; prefix_5&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Array&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [0] =&amp;gt; 1_suffix&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [1] =&amp;gt; 2_suffix&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [2] =&amp;gt; 3_suffix&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [3] =&amp;gt; 4_suffix&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    [4] =&amp;gt; 5_suffix&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Simple and clean solution for prefixing or appending to every element in an array.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
